         <entry xml:id="teraqiyah-dlgenr"
            xml:lang="en"
            type="mainEntry"
            prev="#"
            next="#"
            source="Genesis Rabbah">
            <form type="lemma" opt="false">
               <orth type="lemma" xml:lang="jpa" opt="false" select="true">תרקיה</orth>
               <orth type="transliteration" xml:lang="fjb" opt="false">trqyh</orth>
               <pron notation="rabbinic" opt="false">teraqiyah</pron>
               <gramGrp opt="false">
                  <gram type="pos" opt="false">noun</gram>
                  <gram type="gen" opt="false">f</gram>
               </gramGrp>
               <form type="variant">
                  <orth type="variant" xml:lang="jpa">תרקיא</orth>
                  <orth type="transliteration" xml:lang="fjb">trqyʾ</orth>
                  <pron notation="rabbinic">teraqiaʾ</pron>
               </form>
            </form>
            <sense xml:id="teraqiyah-dlgenr-1">
               <cit type="translation" xml:lang="en" subtype="sense">
                  <quote>vault, breastwork</quote>
               </cit>
               <cit type="translationEquivalent" xml:lang="grc">
                  <quote>θωράκια</quote>
               </cit>
               <cit type="example" xml:lang="jpa">
                  <quote>ר' יצחק ור' שמעון בן לקיש ר' יצחק אמר בשר ודם מותח אהל אננקי על ידי שהות הוא רפי קימאה, ברם הכא התרקיע עמו לשחקים, ואין תאמר שהן רפין תל' לו' חזקים, ריש לקיש אמר בשר ודם מוסך בולוס אננקי על ידי שהות הוא מעלה חלודה ברם הכא חזקים כראי מוצק נראים כמין 
                     <app>
                        <lem>תרקיה</lem>
                        <rdg wit="#Ox2 Vat2">תרקיתם</rdg>
                        <rdg wit="#Ox1">תרקרתן</rdg>
                        <rdg wit="#K">תרקיהם</rdg>
                        <rdg wit="#V">תרקיא</rdg>
                     </app></quote>
                  <bibl>
                     <ref type="witness">12,13</ref>
                     <ref type="witness">I 112: 1</ref>
                  </bibl>
                  <ref type="entry" xml:lang="jpa">בולוס</ref>
                  <ref type="entry" xml:lang="jpa">אננקי</ref>
                  <cit type="translation" xml:lang="en">
                     <quote>R. Yiṣḥaq and R. Shimʿon ben Laqish. R. Yiṣḥaq said: when a man sets up a tent in hurry, after a while it will get slightly slacken, but here: Canst thou with Him spread out the sky? (Hi 37,18) And if you say that they are slack, the Scripture says: strong [as a molten mirror] (ibid.). Resh Laqish said: When a man makes in hurry a casting in form of a round object, after a while it will get rusty, but here: strong as a molten mirror [ibid.] - they [the heavens] look like a breastwork.</quote>
                  </cit>
                  <note>= Yalq 19 [I 60: 23] (<term xml:lang="jpa">תרקיא</term>); Yalq Jes 450 [VII 197: 86] (<term xml:lang="jpa">תרקיא</term>)</note>
               </cit>
            </sense>
            <note>Hapax in Rabb. Lit. Cf. <bibl type="modern">AC VIII 278a</bibl>, <bibl type="modern">Levy IV 675a</bibl>. <bibl type="modern">Jastrow I 558a</bibl>, <bibl type="modern">Krauss, LW II 278b</bibl>: Gr. <term xml:lang="grc">ἀνθρἀκιον</term>. Löw: Gr. <term xml:lang="jpa">θράκιας λίθος</term>. See <bibl type="modern">Epstein (1934) 38</bibl>. See in detail: <bibl type="modern">Drew-Bear (1972) 76</bibl>. Other spellings: <term xml:lang="jpa">טרקיה</term> and <term xml:lang="jpa">טרקיא</term>.</note>
